Package iscteiul.ista

Class PropertyRecord

java.lang.Object
iscteiul.ista.PropertyRecord
public class PropertyRecord extends Object
Represents an immutable record of a property, including its geometry, area, ownership, and location details (parish, municipality, island).

This class is typically instantiated from parsed CSV data. All fields are declared final, ensuring that once a PropertyRecord is created, its values cannot be changed.

  • Constructor Details

    • PropertyRecord

      public PropertyRecord(int objectID, long parcelID, long parcelNumber, double shapeLength, double shapeArea, String geometry, int owner, String parish, String municipality, String island)
      Constructs an immutable PropertyRecord with all required fields.
      Parameters:
      objectID - the unique object identifier (column 0)
      parcelID - the primary parcel ID, possibly parsed from scientific notation (column 1)
      parcelNumber - a secondary parcel code or number (column 2)
      shapeLength - the length of the property's shape (column 3)
      shapeArea - the area of the property (column 4)
      geometry - a geometry representation (e.g., WKT) for the property's boundaries (column 5)
      owner - an integer representing the owner code or ID (column 6)
      parish - the parish (freguesia) name, or null if "NA" (column 7)
      municipality - the municipality name, or null if "NA" (column 8)
      island - the island name, or null if "NA" (column 9)
